text:
The <https://github.com/emptypockets-dev/create-HubSpot-project|create-HubSpot-project utility by emptypockets> can give you a starter project that comes with a working TailwindCSS implementation.

One adjustment you may have to make is ensuring the `content` property in your tailwind.config.js file is set up in a way that catches the modules folder. I typically set it up like:
```module.exports = {
    content: ["./src/**/*.html"],
    ...
}```
